    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 138.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Through the neglect of parents, the youth in our cities are corrupting their ways and polluting their souls before God. This will ever be the fruit of idleness. The almshouses, the prisons, and the gallows publish the sorrowful tale of the neglected duties of parents.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">11<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 9-13-1881\" data-link=\"821.3956\">The Review and Herald, September 13, 1881</span></span></a></sup>",
