    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 138.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Instead of the crowded city seek some retired situation where your children will be, so far as possible, shielded from temptation, and there train and educate them for usefulness. The prophet Ezekiel thus enumerates the causes that led to Sodom&apos;s sin and destruction: &ldquo;Pride, fulness of bread, and abundance of idleness was in her and in her daughters, neither did she strengthen the hand of the poor and needy.&rdquo; All who would escape the doom of Sodom must shun the course that brought God&apos;s judgments upon that wicked city.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">12<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"5T 232.1\" data-link=\"113.1197\">Testimonies for the Church 5:232, 233</span>.</span></a></sup>",
