    "refcode_short": "AH 138.4",
    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 138.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "When Lot entered Sodom, he fully intended to keep himself free from iniquity and to command his household after him. But he signally failed. The corrupting influences about him had an effect upon his own faith, and his children&apos;s connection with the inhabitants of Sodom bound up his interest in a measure with theirs. The result is before us. Many are still making a similar mistake.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 168.1\" data-link=\"84.682\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 168</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 393,
